1. Extract SceneController (highest priority)
Goal
Move all scene lifecycle + switching logic out of MainWindow.
Tasks
 Create SceneController
 Move scene switching logic:
switchToScene
addScene
deleteScene
 Move scene persistence coordination:
SceneStateManager.loadScene
SceneStateManager.saveMaster
 Store:
active scene ID
current SceneState
 Expose events:
onSceneChanged(SceneState newState)
 Remove direct SceneManager usage from UI layer where possible
Result
MainWindow no longer decides how scenes work, only reacts to changes.

2. Extract MapController (interaction + map logic layer)
Goal
Remove all map-related logic from MainWindow.
Tasks
 Create MapController
 Move map interaction logic:
wireMapCanvas
token right-click handling
showTokenContextMenu
 Move map operations:
loadMapFromFile
promptMapWidth
clearMap
clearTokenPositions
 Centralize entity/token sync:
syncTokens
repaint
entityChanged coordination
 Define controller API:
setPendingEntity(Entity e)
removeToken(Token t)
toggleStatus(Token t, String status)
 Ensure MapCanvas is only a rendering surface (no business logic)
Result
MapCanvas becomes “dumb UI”; MapController owns behavior.

3. Extract UIWiringService (pure event wiring layer)
Goal
Eliminate all “glue code” from MainWindow.
Tasks
 Create UIWiringService
 Move all wiring methods:
wireSidebar
wireMapCanvas (event hookup only)
wireScenePanel
 Replace logic with simple bindings:
Sidebar → MapController
ScenePanel → SceneController
MapCanvas → MapController callbacks
 Ensure NO business logic exists here:
no state changes
no file loading
no UI decisions
 Make wiring explicit and restartable:
bind(SceneController, MapController, UIComponents)
Result
You can rewire UI without touching logic.

4. Reduce MainWindow to “composition root”
Goal
Make MainWindow only responsible for layout + startup.
Tasks
 Remove scene logic (delegated to SceneController)
 Remove map logic (delegated to MapController)
 Remove wiring logic (delegated to UIWiringService)
 Keep only:
UI creation (BorderPane, SplitPane)
controller instantiation
initial wiring call
 Replace direct calls like:
switchToScene
loadMapFromFile
showTokenContextMenu
 Replace with controller method calls or events
Target state:
MainWindow becomes ~200–300 lines max and mostly declarative.

5. Fix state ownership clarity (very important hidden issue)
Goal
Ensure only ONE layer owns mutation.
Tasks
 Decide ownership rules:
SceneController owns SceneState switching
MapController owns map mutation
SceneState is passive data only
 Remove duplicate mutation paths:
avoid syncTokens, entityChanged, repaint being called from random places
 Introduce single update flow:
“state changed → controller notifies UI → UI refresh”

6. Decouple ScenePanel from SceneState
Goal
Stop UI from directly depending on mutable state objects.
Tasks
 ScenePanel talks only to SceneController
 Remove direct SceneState references where possible
 Replace with:
SceneSummary DTOs (id, name, order)
 ScenePanel becomes stateless renderer of scene list

7. Standardize event flow direction
Goal
Prevent circular dependencies (your current hidden issue source).
Define rule:
UI → Controller → State → Controller → UI update
Tasks
 Enforce no UI → UI direct updates (except rendering)
 Enforce no Controller → Controller direct UI calls
 Use callbacks/events only

8. Remove “MainWindow owns everything” pattern
Goal
Break hidden coupling.
Tasks
 Remove fields from MainWindow that belong to controllers:
SceneState
SceneManager
direct manipulation of MapCanvas logic
 Replace with:
sceneController.getState()
mapController.getCanvas()
 Ensure MainWindow does not mutate state












Save All / Load Project / Reset
Design
 Define project folder structure
 Define project.json schema
 Decide logging storage policy (project vs external)
Core implementation
 Create ProjectStateManager
 Implement saveProject()
 Implement loadProject()
 Implement resetProject()
Integration
 Add “Save Project” menu item → calls saveProject()
 Add “Load Project…” file picker → calls loadProject()
 Add “Reset Project” with confirmation dialog
Safety / UX
 Add overwrite warning for Save All if needed
 Add confirmation + backup suggestion for Reset
 Ensure UI fully rebuilds after load/reset